        "checksum": "78036ac5cd4720dc39d123e4b2e64d05fc224445132ee327e805edc4439a779b_1_1_1_0__1",
        "ggHIYFkwWAg_text": "<strong>Stop treating the symptom. Fix what's causing it.</strong>",
        "ggOfx0BOCTo_background_desktop_image_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Design_sans_titre_56.jpg",
        "ggOfx0BOCTo_background_desktop_videoHtml5": "https://media.w3.org/2010/05/sintel/trailer.mp4",
        "ggOfx0BOCTo_background_mobile_image_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/BANNER_MOBILE_88_fe844808-d56f-4362-91d0-b0082b2d5eb5.jpg",
        "ggOfx0BOCTo_background_mobile_videoHtml5": "https://media.w3.org/2010/05/sintel/trailer.mp4",
        "ggaptQJNyJt_label": "<p><strong>Try Solydia Risk-Free</strong></p>",
        "ggfNpjlhu9r_text": "<p>Full S3 protection at 460g. Kevlar sole. Deep cushioning. Proper arch support. Free Comfort Pack included.</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262330389594795"
    },
    "gp_section_613262330389791403": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "09f7d815fba7b4ead4886005339fa8610f5cbb57dd5e078b0136064e40308da9_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg3krvjK2yb_text": "1.Every step in a 1kg boot is a hammer blow to your fascia",
        "gg5jp5xOybH_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "ggezJjNqnNl_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggezJjNqnNl_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "ggyTRmUd0ss_text": "<p>The average safety boot weighs over 1kg per foot. On a standard shift, that's somewhere between 8,000 and 12,000 steps — <strong>8 to 12 tonnes of extra load</strong> your plantar fascia absorbs every day compared to a lighter shoe.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Your fascia is a thin band of tissue. It wasn't built for that kind of repeated impact on concrete. Over months, it develops micro-tears faster than your body can repair them. That's when the stabbing pain starts.</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262330389791403"
    },
    "gp_section_613262330390119083": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "6815c6b929f4b7cbb8bf233c963f5752083c485714cb82ace0cd596fc4d51f83_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg4t8aUY-gP_text": "5 Reasons Your Safety Boots Are Making Your Plantar Fasciitis <i>Worse</i>",
        "ggyV04MX_qM_text": "<p>If that first step out of bed feels like standing on broken glass — your boots aren't just failing you.</p><p><i><strong>They're the reason it's getting worse.</strong></i></p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262330390119083"
    },
    "gp_section_613262330390184619": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "7358866cce2cf44f32bf2aaddbfbcac49b35387f1074926dc77b2be697f41385_1_1_1_0__1",
        "section_preload": "true"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262330390184619"
    },
    "gp_section_613262847194956443": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "a7f84e417d1a05d13ec42ae1789e773fccaf5be4f8b588ec43470ef4ea342ba2_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg-Zoru5Pem_text": "<p><strong>RYAN S.</strong> <span style=\"color:#B4B4B4;font-size:13px;\">/ Design Director</span></p>",
        "gg6Eq4NPZYb_alt": "Alt Image",
        "gg6Eq4NPZYb_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/ec0a9c3f-ba6f-4db1-aab0-1f2a1f15f8ce/-/format/auto/",
        "gg6Eq4NPZYb_title": "Image Title",
        "gg8c3cOrkAU_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "ggAFHxVnklR_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggAFHxVnklR_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/c90e5b61-8513-4914-9c30-40a1950282e2/-/format/auto/",
        "ggAFHxVnklR_title": "Image Title",
        "ggEcdY3_Vmm_text": "<p>Before I got proper boots with arch support I experienced same thing you're talking about. The pain just kept getting worse every year.</p>",
        "ggKRJS2bPeK_text": "2.Steel sole plates lock your arch in the worst possible position",
        "ggTzRT1nq5R_text": "<p>Traditional safety boots use a steel anti-puncture plate in the sole — not the toe cap, the plate underneath your foot. It stops nails going through. But it also <strong>stops your foot from flexing naturally.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Your arch is designed to load and unload with every step, distributing pressure evenly. A steel plate forces it flat — concentrating all the pressure on the exact spot where the fascia connects to the heel bone. Exactly where it hurts most.</p>",
        "ggkefxVCvN0_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggkefxVCvN0_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262847194956443"
    },
    "gp_section_613262864978805403": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "d194b6b46ced1bb52bb6270cc024dcd5355b5bac9ba3132a74a41e82cd0ebaab_1_1_1_0__1",
        "ggN8g8R-wbF_text": "<p>Concrete draws moisture out of leather — it's why concrete always feels cold underfoot. Over weeks, this dries and hardens the leather in your boots. <strong>The cushioning degrades. The structure stiffens.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>By the time your boots feel \"broken in,\" they've already lost most of the shock absorption your feet need. And replacing them every few months isn't realistic.</p>",
        "ggNNWcelSJ-_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggNNWcelSJ-_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section4.webp",
        "ggPtOX0sltE_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section4.webp",
        "ggr1cmYIdjg_text": "3.Concrete kills your boots from the inside — and your feet pay for it"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262864978805403"
    },
    "gp_section_613262864995582619": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "de58188f5ff378296acba29cd3fee052b18448bb8b5a7f1a925b90a85f8fd793_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg7rw_7YFz-_text": "<p>Gel insoles, frozen water bottles, calf stretches, podiatrist visits. They help for an hour. Maybe two. <strong>Then you go back to standing on concrete in a rigid, heavy boot — and the damage starts again.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>It's like icing a bruise every night and hitting the same spot with a hammer every morning.</p>",
        "ggAb1M-o5js_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggAb1M-o5js_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "ggCBkuWNuL6_text": "4.Insoles and ice don't fix the thing that's causing the damage",
        "ggUyxs8P0dp_text": "<p>I've been multiple times to the podiatrist with his custom insoles — no help. Chiropractor at £50 a visit for several weeks, nothing to show for it. Podiatrist just wants to do surgery and I can't take that kind of time off work.</p>",
        "ggcaBDUx2QZ_text": "<p><strong>RYAN S.</strong> <span style=\"color:#B4B4B4;font-size:13px;\">/ Design Director</span></p>",
        "ggexYmSmRX4_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggexYmSmRX4_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/c90e5b61-8513-4914-9c30-40a1950282e2/-/format/auto/",
        "ggexYmSmRX4_title": "Image Title",
        "ggqZ5pV16bS_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "gguycGijizz_alt": "Alt Image",
        "gguycGijizz_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/ec0a9c3f-ba6f-4db1-aab0-1f2a1f15f8ce/-/format/auto/",
        "gguycGijizz_title": "Image Title"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262864995582619"
    },
    "gp_section_613262884574593840": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "184526abe7b60057aec5b1f2a94140aaad5f254b891005668d40f0631babadcb_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg1qGFhcpMp_text": "<p>So many things I used to get done after work — now I just hobble in the house trying to find somewhere to sit and get my feet up. All while getting nothing else done unless I force myself to.</p>",
        "gg7ooPBT3nx_alt": "Alt Image",
        "gg7ooPBT3nx_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/c90e5b61-8513-4914-9c30-40a1950282e2/-/format/auto/",
        "gg7ooPBT3nx_title": "Image Title",
        "ggFT9mZTK9D_text": "<p>PF is progressive. The micro-tears multiply. Scar tissue builds up. The pain that used to fade by mid-morning starts lasting all day. <strong>By midday, you're limping. By end of shift, every step is agony.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The longer you spend in boots that don't support your foot properly, the harder it becomes to reverse.</p>",
        "ggF_y-6Ui2X_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggF_y-6Ui2X_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp",
        "ggFqUy1PcB2_text": "<p><strong>RYAN S.</strong> <span style=\"color:#B4B4B4;font-size:13px;\">/ Design Director</span></p>",
        "ggSziYtgDC9_text": "5.Plantar fasciitis doesn't stay the same — it gets worse",
        "ggrv1W0IkmZ_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggrv1W0IkmZ_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://ucarecdn.com/ec0a9c3f-ba6f-4db1-aab0-1f2a1f15f8ce/-/format/auto/",
        "ggrv1W0IkmZ_title": "Image Title",
        "ggw2GzTRjEr_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/section1.webp"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-613262884574593840"
    },
    "gp_section_613294853912003243": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "770ef9646f0b445b05f9551f7cd1f59e44f85f1898ead66f4a7888239fa3c617_1_1_1_0__1",
        "gg-NTnyYnag_text": "<p>15,000+</p>",
        "ggJq87taCGy_text": "<p>Per shoe</p>",
        "ggSBjvRq55R_text": "<p>Certified</p>",
        "ggTP7aCPqZt_text": "<p>Per shoe</p>",
        "ggTTICJJe_r_text": "<p>460g</p>",
        "ggTWKUF4t9L_text": "<p>Workers switched</p>",
        "ggZZTdY21Jm_text": "<p><strong>460g</strong></p>",
        "ggpCzFxpGAW_text": "<p>S3</p>",
        "ggtr25Ugtq9_text": "<p>&nbsp;Gel insoles. Frozen water bottles. Calf stretches &nbsp;before every shift. Maybe even a podiatrist at &nbsp;£50 a visit.<br><br><strong>&nbsp;It still comes back every morning.</strong> Because &nbsp;these fixes treat the symptom — not what's &nbsp;causing the damage 8 hours a day.</p>"
      },
